30. non est quod multa loquamur: there is no need to say much, i. e. the conclusion is obvious.

32. ad summum fortunae. ‘We have attained all that is possible to human nature; we can beat the Greeks at their accomplishments.' Achivis doctius unctis shows that this is said with some irony, as though he had added ‘as much as we can in our own more solid excellences.’
